The paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) techniques, specifically Automated Planning, in Business Process Management (BPM). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the different stages of the BPM life cycle, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper mentions the increasing amounts of data that influence the execution of process instances, which could place it in cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the need for reactivity and flexibility in BPM systems, which could place it in cs.CY (Cybernetics). Finally, the paper mentions successful applications of automated planning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
